This project is deployment/orchestration tooling. It does NOT redistribute the
model weights, the serving container image, or the upstream vLLM/kernel source
it builds on — those are pulled at build time from their own repositories, each
under its own license. This project orchestrates and documents them.

Attributed upstreams:

  - vLLM                         (Apache-2.0)   — the inference engine. The current
                                   default lane pins v0.25.1; the prior lane pinned
                                   0.21.x. Upstream PR #47356 is vendored as a source
                                   patch for the 0.25.1 lane (patches/vllm-pr47356-vgx10/).
  - DeepSeek-V4-Flash-DSpark     — model weights, by DeepSeek AI, under the
                                   license stated on its Hugging Face model card
  - anemll                       — the dspark-vllm-gx10 community GB10 port (the
                                   digest-pinned vLLM 0.25.1 base image this kit
                                   pulls for the current default lane)
  - b12x                         — the MXFP4 MoE kernel package used by the GB10
                                   serving images (VLLM_USE_B12X_MOE)
  - FlashInfer                   (Apache-2.0)   — the top-k/top-p sampler. The 0.25.1
                                   base carries FlashInfer 0.6.15-dev, which already
                                   includes PR #3615 (commit 49f2abf), the SM120/121
                                   multi-CTA radix top-k reset-race fix; the prior
                                   0.21.x lane vendors that same PR as a source patch
                                   (patches/flashinfer-pr3615/).
  - tonyd2wild                   — the 2x-DGX-Spark NVFP4/DSpark serving recipe the
                                   prior 0.21.x lane vendors and pins (docker-compose)
  - drowzeys ("Keys")            — the DSpark concurrency patch, nvfp4_ds_mla KV,
                                   and the sm121a sparse-MLA / dual-cache work
  - aidendle94                   — the compiled GB10 (sm_121a) DeepGEMM and
                                   sparse-MLA kernels shipped inside the prior lane's image
  - MiaAI-Lab                    — dual-Spark packaging and worker-first launch
  - rafaelcaricio                — DSpark vLLM integration
  - NVIDIA dgx-spark-playbooks   — the official "connect two Sparks" guidance

These components are single-author, fast-moving, community efforts and are
provided by their authors without warranty. Validate on your own hardware.
